      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "In Eclipse it is possible to make the IDE add a static import for methods. This is done by adding the <code>Collectors</code> class in <i>Preferences</i> -&gt; <i>Java</i> -&gt; <i>Editor</i> -&gt; <i>Content Assist</i> -&gt; <i>Favorites</i>. After this, you only have to type <code>toLi</code> at hit <i>Ctr+Space</i> to have the IDE fill in <code>toList</code> and add the static import."
