    "body" : "<p>You can use the collect method:</p>\n\n<pre><code>IntStream.of(1, 2, 3).collect(ArrayList::new, List::add, List::addAll);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>In fact, this is almost exactly what Java is doing when you call .collect(Collectors.toList()) on an object stream:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static &lt;T&gt; Collector&lt;T, ?, List&lt;T&gt;&gt; toList() {\n    return new Collectors.CollectorImpl(ArrayList::new, List::add, (var0, var1) -&gt; {\n        var0.addAll(var1);\n        return var0;\n    }, CH_ID);\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note: The third parameter is only required if you want to run parallel collection; for sequential collection providing just the first two will suffice.</p>\n"
  } ],
